main event: An unidentified object, described as the size of a golf ball, was reported flying east at 1815 hours on 19 September 1965.
interesting points: The object was white and yellow with no tail or exhaust,It made no sound during observation,The object was observed using binoculars and could also be seen clearly with the naked eye,The sighting lasted about 5 to 10 minutes as it gradually moved out of sight,The individual reporting the sighting was deemed reliable by Navy personnel.
sighted object: round object the size of a golf ball
witness description: E.E.N. Shields, Yokohama Shore Patrol, US Navy Housing Activity
